trans-unit.source: Generates a basic descriptive statistics report for the columns in a dataset
trans-unit.target: Generates a basic descriptive statistics report for the columns in a dataset

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Descriptive Statistics</ui> module to create a set of standard statistical measures that describe each column in the input table.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Descriptive Statistics</ui> module to create a set of standard statistical measures that describe each column in the input table.

trans-unit.source: The module does not return the original dataset.
trans-unit.target: The module does not return the original dataset.

trans-unit.source: Instead, it generates a row for each column, beginning with the column name and followed by relevant statistics for that column, based on its data type.
trans-unit.target: Instead, it generates a row for each column, beginning with the column name and followed by relevant statistics for that column, based on its data type.

trans-unit.source: Such reports are useful when you want to understand the characteristics of the complete dataset.
trans-unit.target: Such reports are useful when you want to understand the characteristics of the complete dataset.

trans-unit.source: For example, you might need to know:
trans-unit.target: For example, you might need to know:

trans-unit.source: How many missing values are there in each column?
trans-unit.target: How many missing values are there in each column?

trans-unit.source: How many unique categorical values are there in a feature column?
trans-unit.target: How many unique categorical values are there in a feature column?

trans-unit.source: What is the mean and standard deviation of the column?
trans-unit.target: What is the mean and standard deviation of the column?

trans-unit.source: You can get a partial list of statistics by using the <ui>Visualize</ui> option in any module that outputs a dataset, but the visualization includes only some top number of rows.
trans-unit.target: You can get a partial list of statistics by using the <ui>Visualize</ui> option in any module that outputs a dataset, but the visualization includes only some top number of rows.

trans-unit.source: By outputting the statistics in a tabular report, you can use the data in BI reporting tools or provide the values as input to another custom operation in the experiment.
trans-unit.target: By outputting the statistics in a tabular report, you can use the data in BI reporting tools or provide the values as input to another custom operation in the experiment.

trans-unit.source: You can use <ui>Descriptive Statistics</ui> to calculate statistics on dense or sparse columns.
trans-unit.target: You can use <ui>Descriptive Statistics</ui> to calculate statistics on dense or sparse columns.

trans-unit.source: The columns that you select as input can contain numeric, Boolean, or other values.
trans-unit.target: The columns that you select as input can contain numeric, Boolean, or other values.

trans-unit.source: For numeric and Boolean columns, this module calculates statistics such as means, medians, modes, and standard deviations.
trans-unit.target: For numeric and Boolean columns, this module calculates statistics such as means, medians, modes, and standard deviations.

trans-unit.source: The module calculates these statistics on the assumption that the statistical instances belong to a representative sample of a population.
trans-unit.target: The module calculates these statistics on the assumption that the statistical instances belong to a representative sample of a population.

trans-unit.source: For non-numeric columns, only the values for <legacyBold>Count</legacyBold>, <legacyBold>Unique value count</legacyBold>, and <legacyBold>Missing value count</legacyBold> are computed.
trans-unit.target: For non-numeric columns, only the values for <legacyBold>Count</legacyBold>, <legacyBold>Unique value count</legacyBold>, and <legacyBold>Missing value count</legacyBold> are computed.

trans-unit.source: For other statistics, a null value is returned.
trans-unit.target: For other statistics, a null value is returned.

trans-unit.source: Columns that contain Boolean values are processed as follows:
trans-unit.target: Columns that contain Boolean values are processed as follows:

trans-unit.source: When calculating <legacyBold>Min</legacyBold>, a logical AND is applied.
trans-unit.target: When calculating <legacyBold>Min</legacyBold>, a logical AND is applied.

trans-unit.source: When calculating <legacyBold>Max</legacyBold>, a logical OR is applied.
trans-unit.target: When calculating <legacyBold>Max</legacyBold>, a logical OR is applied.

trans-unit.source: When computing <legacyBold>Range</legacyBold>, the module first checks whether the number of unique values in the column equals 2.
trans-unit.target: When computing <legacyBold>Range</legacyBold>, the module first checks whether the number of unique values in the column equals 2.

trans-unit.source: When computing any statistic that requires floating-point calculations, values of True are treated as 1.0, and values of False are treated as 0.0.
trans-unit.target: When computing any statistic that requires floating-point calculations, values of True are treated as 1.0, and values of False are treated as 0.0.
